Amurka ta kamata ta ba da gudummawa ga ayyukan A.I. sau biyu
Kai-Fu Lee, wani mai zuba jari kuma masanin kimiyyar kere kere da ya yi aiki a Google, Microsoft da Apple, ya ce yayin da China ke kara shiga cikin batun yin amfani da fasaha, ya kamata Amurka ta ninka kudaden da take bayarwa a fannin.
Yawancin ra'ayoyi daga sassa daban-daban na gwamnatin Amurka sun yi sharhi game da shirin AI, duk da cewa Amurka gabaɗaya ba ta da tsarin dabarun AI na hukuma.
A daidai wannan lokacin, China ta gabatar da shirinta a bara: tana son zama mai jagorantar fasahar AI nan da shekarar 2030.
"Biyu na kudade don binciken AI kyakkyawan farawa ne saboda sauran ƙasashe suna nesa da Amurka kuma muna neman sabbin dama a cikin AI", in ji Lee.
Lee ya gaya wa tashar talabijin ta CNBC a cikin wata hira a wannan makon cewa samun kudade biyu na iya haɓaka damar samun babbar nasarar AI ta gaba da za a yi a Amurka.
Lee, editan littafin "Matsanancin ƙarfin AI: China, Silicon Valley da Sabon Tsarin Duniya", wanda aka buga a wannan watan, Houghton Mifflin Harcourt, Shugaba na Sinovation Ventures, wanda ya saka hannun jari a cikin ɗayan manyan kamfanonin AI a China, Face ++.
A cikin shekarun 1980 a Jami'ar Carnegie Mellon, ya yi aiki a kan tsarin AI wanda ya ci nasara a saman wasan American Othello, kuma daga baya ya kasance babban jami'in gudanarwa a Microsoft Research kuma shugaban ofishin reshe a China.
Lee ya amince da kalubale na fasaha na gwamnatin Amurka a baya, kamar shirin ci gaban mutum na hukumar bincike mai zurfi ta tsaron kasa, kuma ya nemi wani lokaci na gaba don taimakawa wajen gano makomar hangen nesa.
Lee ya ce masu bincike a Amurka galibi suna da wahalar neman tallafin gwamnati.
"Ba kasar Sin ce ke cire shugabannin ilimi ba, kasuwanci ne", in ji Lee.
Facebook, Google da sauran kamfanonin fasaha sun yi hayar masu tasiri daga jami'o'i da dama don yin aiki a kan ayyukan AI a cikin 'yan shekarun nan.
