Kasar Sin ta sanar da karuwar kashi 14 cikin 100 na yawan 'yan kasarta da ke rayuwa da cutar HIV da cutar kanjamau.
Ma'aikatan kiwon lafiya sun ce fiye da mutane dubu 820 ne ke fama da cutar a kasar.
An samu sabbin mutane kusan 40,000 a cikin kwata na biyu na 2018 kadai.
Yawancin sababbin cututtuka sun kamu da cutar ta hanyar jima'i, ba kamar yadda aka saba ba.
A baya dai cutar HIV ta yadu cikin sauri a wasu yankuna na kasar Sin, saboda jinin da aka yi wa jini.
Jami'an lafiya na kasar Sin sun bayyana hakan a wani taro a lardin Yunnan inda suka ce adadin wadanda suka kamu da cutar ta hanyar wannan hanya ya kai kusan sifili.
Duk da haka, shekara shekara, adadin mutanen da ke rayuwa da cutar HIV da cutar kanjamau a China ya karu zuwa 100,000.
Cutar HIV ta hanyar jima'i na da matukar rikitarwa a cikin al'ummar 'yan luwadi (LGBT) na kasar Sin.
An dakatar da yin luwadi a kasar Sin tun shekarar 1997, amma ana ci gaba da nuna bambanci ga LGBT.
Saboda dabi'un da suka dace da al'adun gargajiya na kasar, bincike ya kiyasta cewa daga kashi 70 zuwa 90% na mazajen da suke yin jima'i da maza za su yi aure da mata.
Yawancin cututtuka na cutar suna faruwa ne saboda rashin kariya ta jima'i a cikin waɗannan alaƙar.
Tun 2003, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi alkawarin samar da maganin cutar HIV a matsayin wani bangare na kokarin magance matsalar.
